I’m digging for Fossils right now. Want to dig
{pageend:with me?}
There just might be another dig spot close by...

{pageend:Oh?}
{pageend:There is a note tucked inside the Explorer Kit.}
{pageend:“Digging for Fossils!}
“I’ve put a sledgehammer and pickax in your
Explorer Kit. Use them, and you’ll be able to
dig out all sorts of stuff from the walls—
{pageend:before the wall comes tumbling down, that is!}
“I’m sure you can do it! Good luck, youngster!”

{pageend:...}
The wall started to crumble.
It’s too dangerous to go in.

{pageend:The Grand Underground is really massive!}
You should keep your eye on the map as you go
so you don’t get lost.

{pageend:The Underground is divided into separate zones.}
If you want to go to a different zone, you should
go up to the surface first!

{pageend:Have you found a Pokémon Hideaway yet?}
There are lots of Pokémon there,
so keep looking!

{pageend:I made a Secret Base all for myself!}
You can bore a hole in a wall with the
Digger Drill to build your own.

{pageend:You can place statues in your Secret Base.}
Apparently something good will happen if you
place lots of them.

You can set pedestals for the statues you place
{pageend:in your Secret Base.}
If you’ve got a pedestal, go ahead and try it.

There are all sorts of things buried in the
{pageend:walls of the Underground.}
Sometimes you’ll even find treasure!

When you’re digging for Fossils, watch out for
{pageend:cracks in the wall!}
If you dig too much, the wall will collapse.

Sometimes when you’re digging in the walls,
{pageend:you’ll find a Mysterious Shard.}
What do you suppose they’re used for?

{pageend:There are a few different types of stone boxes.}
The prettier the box, the rarer the statue you’ll
find inside.

{pageend:It’s a good idea to collect lots of spheres.}
You can exchange them for all sorts of things
with some folks in the Underground.

{pageend:Spheres come in large and small sizes.}
The larger spheres are rare, so you’re
lucky if you find one!

